sub_unit.name: Essex
sub_unit.note: The New-Jersey Journal (Elizabethtown, NJ) October 18, 1814 lists totals as: Henry Southard 2822 votes, Ephraim Bateman 2817 votes, Ezra Baker 2810 votes, Benjamin Bennett 2812 votes, John Frelinghuysen 607 votes, James Parker 601 votes, James Giles 594 votes, Samuel W. Harrison 503 votes, Jacob S. Thompson 597 votes.

sub_unit.name: Middlesex
sub_unit.note: "432 votes were given in Middlesex for Jacob I. Thompson, which were doubtless intended for Jacob S. Thompson." New-Jersey Journal (Elizabethtown, NJ). October 25, 1814.
